## **3.6 Hands-On Practice ‚Äì Guides & Installation**

### **Lab 1: Exploring AWS Free Tier (IaaS & PaaS)**

1. **Sign Up for AWS Free Tier**
    
    - Go to [AWS Free Tier](https://aws.amazon.com/free/) and create an account.
        
2. **Launch an EC2 Instance (IaaS)**
    
    - Follow the [AWS EC2 Quick Start Guide](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/EC2_GetStarted.html).
        
3. **Deploy a Web Application with Elastic Beanstalk (PaaS)**
    
    - Follow [AWS Elastic Beanstalk Guide](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticbeanstalk/latest/dg/Welcome.html).
        

---

### **Lab 2: Exploring Google Cloud (Hybrid Cloud)**

1. **Sign Up for Google Cloud Free Tier**
    
    - Visit [Google Cloud Free Tier](https://cloud.google.com/free) and get started.
        
2. **Create a Google Compute Engine VM (IaaS)**
    
    - Follow [Google Cloud Compute Engine Guide](https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/quickstart-linux).
        
3. **Deploy a Google Kubernetes Engine Cluster (Hybrid)**
    
    - Use [Google Kubernetes Engine Docs](https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs).
        

---

### **Lab 3: Exploring Azure Cloud (Private & Hybrid Cloud)**

1. **Sign Up for Azure Free Tier**
    
    - Visit [Azure Free Account](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/free/) to create your free account.
        
2. **Create a Virtual Machine (IaaS)**
    
    - Follow [Create an Azure VM Tutorial](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machines/windows/quick-create-portal).
        
3. **Use Azure Stack for Hybrid Cloud**
    
    - Learn about [Azure Stack](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/overview/azure-stack/).
        

---

## üìò **Summary**

- **IaaS, PaaS, SaaS** are the three main cloud service models, each offering varying levels of control and abstraction over cloud resources.
    
- **Public, Private, Hybrid, and Community Clouds** offer different deployment options, based on factors like security, compliance, and cost.
    
- Choosing the right cloud model depends on the business needs such as scalability, security, and customization requirements.
    

